# 1. 大切な思い出を

Soft Tennis Club Captain: Okay, that's all for today's practice! Good work, everyone!
Saki: Good work today!
Saki: Phew... That sure was a workout!
Saki: (I haven't been able to do club stuff much lately since we've been busy doing that show and getting our contracts sorted...)
Saki: (But it really is great to get my body moving!)
???: Hello, everyone!
Saki: Huh?! Is that...?
Third Year Student A: Hehe, it's been a while! Sorry to drop in out of the blue.
Soft Tennis Club Members: Oh! You came to visit us?!
Saki: It's you! It's been so long!
Third Year Student B: Oh, Saki! Looks like you're doing well.
Saki: I am! Hehe, I'm happy to see you again after so long!
Saki: Oh, but what brings you here today? It's great to see you at practice again...!
Third Year Student B: Well... It's almost graduation for us, y'know? So, we figured we'd show our faces around here one last time.
Saki: Oh...
Saki: Right... Once you graduate, you won't be coming by to see us like this very much...
Soft Tennis Club Members: Yeah... We'll miss you...
Third Year Student A: Hey now, don't give us those sad looks!
Third Year Student B: She's right! We came here to take a picture with you, after all!
Saki: A picture?
Third Year Student A: Yeah. We're actually putting a photo album together.
Third Year Student A: We wanted one of our own, not just the yearbook!
Third Year Student B: We want to be sure that the fun memories we've made will last.
Saki: Your memories...
Third Year Student B: Yup! I mean, we'll always be able to remember them if we've got a photo album, right?
Third Year Student B: Those times we all had ice cream at the convenience store after practice, or took Print Stickers together, all of that.
Third Year Student B: That's why we want to take a picture with all of you today! How about it?
Soft Tennis Club Members: Of course! And please send us the picture too!
Saki: (Making sure your precious memories last... That's a wonderful thing to keep in mind.)
Saki: (Oh yeah, speaking of photo albums...!)
Saki: Hmm, where did I write it...? I think it was on one of the later pages...
Saki: Here it is! Number 95 on my “List of 100 Things to Do Once I'm Back in School”!
Saki: “Make lots of fun memories and put them in a photo album!”
Saki: Hehe, this really takes me back...
Saki: It was right around the end of the school year when I wrote this... They were talking about yearbooks and stuff on TV, and I really wanted one.
Saki: I couldn't hang out with friends while I was in the hospital, so... I also wished I could make enough memories one day to put together an album...
Saki: But now... I've made lots of fun memories.
Saki: Playing in a band with Ichi and the others, studying in a classroom with everyone, not to mention participating in every school event, like the Seaside School and the field trip...
Third Year Student B: We want to be sure that the fun memories we've made will last.
Saki: I also wanna treasure the memories I've made with everyone forever...
Saki: Alright!
Saki: I'm gonna make my very own album just like my seniors!
Saki: Oh, but... There are still some things left to do on my list.
Saki: Like, “Have a sleepover and fall asleep while chatting!” and “Eat crepes on Takeue Street”... I bet it'd be fun to do these with everyone!
Saki: I did have a sleepover with Ichi and the others a while ago, but we stayed up until morning that time, so we'll have to do it again!
Saki: Hehe. I always wanted to do that thing where you ask your friends, “Hey, are you still awake?”♪
Saki: If I'm making an album, I should do all this stuff and take pictures for it!
Saki: Let's see... About how many things are there left to do?
Saki: One, two, three... Oh!
Saki: “Take classes with everyone for a year.” Hehehe, this one deserves a biiig check mark♪
Saki: “Make a lot of friends” is also done... And I went to Yokohama on the field trip, so I'll give “Go someplace far away to have fun” a check!
Saki: I haven't been looking at this notebook much since I've been busy with band stuff lately, but...
Saki: Look how many things I wanted to do that I've accomplished without even realizing...!
Saki: Let's see, how many others have I not finished yet...?
Saki: So about twenty more, huh...?
Saki: If that's all, it might actually be pretty easy to finish them all off if I tried...!
Saki: Alright! I'm gonna accomplish aaall the stuff I wanted to do, take lots of pictures and make them into an awesome album!
Saki: First up is... Oh, this one should be good♪
